<hl>
<seg id=1> Foreign Cooperation in China's Building Material Industry Expands Fast </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Bejing, March 9(xinhua correspondent Li Jianming)-China's building materials industry takes foreign cooperation as an important measure for development. At present foreign capital using sectors in the industry are increasing as the total foreign capitals attracted amounted to 5 billion US dollars. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Now China's building material industry has started a package of cement production projects both in Tonglin, Anhui Province and Xiangxiang, Hunan Province with loans from World Bank and Asia Bank, said an official in charge from the State Building Material Bureau when interviewed today. </seg>
<seg id=4> More foreign funds are flowing into the areas of new materials, high and advanced techniques and materials finely processing. </seg>
<seg id=5> The technology transform project high-grade lavatory facilities pottery, set up with US$100 million of favorable export credit provided by Italy, is making great progress in Shanxi, Shandong, Guangdong, Jilin, Hunan and etc. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> Recently, China building materials sectors have reached some bilateral cooperation agreements with governmental sectors as well as transnational companies of Netherlands, Germany, Thailand, Greek, Australia, Japan, France and Denmark, a lot of new foreign trade partners added. </seg>
<seg id=7> Last year, China's building materials exports valued over US$2100 million. 12 million tons of cement were exported, 46% up the year before, creating a record in history </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> In addition, with the predeposition kiln production line imported in recent years, China has established some large cement manufacturers such as Jidong, Ningguo,Huaihai, Liuzhou and etc, increasing the annual cement production capability by 22 million tons </seg>
</p>
